data.title: Prison Confessions of Gypsy Rose Blanchard: How to watch Lifetime movie for free
data.meta_description: The six-hour special, "Prison Confessions of Gypsy Rose Blanchard," features unprecedented access to Gypsy Rose Blanchard.
data.text:
The six-hour special, “Prison Confessions of Gypsy Rose Blanchard,” features unprecedented access to Gypsy Rose Blanchard and is available to stream on Lifetime.

Viewers looking to stream it for free can do so by using Philo or DirecTV Stream. Both streaming services offer free trials for new users.

WATCH PRISON CONFESSIONS OF GYPSY ROSE BLANCHARD FOR FREE HERE

According to Lifetime, the six-hour special features unprecedented access to Gypsy Rose Blanchard, a victim of Munchausen Syndrome by Proxy who suffered horrific abuse and made national headlines for her role in her mother’s violent murder. Gypsy’s shocking story has been told by many others but now she is finally ready to tell her truth as she becomes a free woman for the first time in her life.

Munchausen syndrome by proxy is a mental illness and a form of child abuse, according to MedlinePlus. The caretaker of a child, most often a mother, either makes up fake symptoms or causes real symptoms to make it look like the child is sick. How can I watch “Prison Confessions of Gypsy Rose Blanchard” without cable?

The Lifetime movie aired on Friday, January 5 on Lifetime and is available to stream on Philo and DirecTV Stream. Both streaming services offer free trials for new users.

What is Philo?

Philo is an over-the-top internet live TV streaming service that offers 60+ entertainment and lifestyle channels, like AMC, BET, MTV, Comedy Central and more, for the budget-friendly price of $25/month.
